Box Plot¶

In [16]:
for x in h.columns:
    plt.figure(figsize = (8,5))
    h.boxplot(column = [x])
    plt.title(f'Box Plot for {x}')
    plt.ylabel('Values')

for x in h.columns:
    h.hist(column = [x], color = 'purple', edgecolor='hotpink')
    plt.title(f'Histogram for {x}')
  • There is no missing values inside the dataset
In [18]:
col = ['CRIM', 'ZN', 'INDUS', 'CHAS', 'NOX', 'RM', 'AGE', 'DIS', 'RAD',
       'TAX', 'PTRATIO', 'B', 'LSTAT', 'MEDV', 'CAT. MEDV']

for i in range(len(col) - 1):
    x = col[i]
    y = col[i+1]
    plt.scatter(x=h[x], y=h[y], color='yellow')
    plt.title(f'Scatter Plot for {x} vs {y}')
    plt.xlabel(x)
    plt.ylabel(y)
    plt.show()
